	   <tr><td colspan=2>I do support the argument that many people are often greedy WHILE knowing that the items really isn't better for them..... for example if i saw a breastplate with 100hp and no other stats I might think, &quot;hey, if im being shot with a spell it wont matter what my ac and stats are (ignoring resist), so why don't I pick up this breastplate for whenever im specifically being shot from a spell but not being meleed so on and so on.&quot; If i really thought this, I might just roll on it not realizing that it may be WAY better for someone else. This mantle is INCREDIBLY nice for a caster and arguably decent(at best) for a melee. Sure for certain instances if you need dex for a trait, but for an overall always used items, it owns for casters, nuf said.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>     As for mantles that you can use.... giving and taking weight in some instances: engraved bone pauldrons, jade inlaid spaulders, acrylia reinforced mantle, mantle of absorbtion, acrylia studded mantle, quite a few others. Personally my monk is 50/50 decision on the engraved bone pauldrons (if he can afford weight) and Acrylia reinforced mantle which is geared more towards stamina/hp and less ac, it also is quite lighter at .3 weight.      <br>     This mantle does not excel in any particular stat for non-INT casters really, this mantle has no stand-out stats for melee. It has INT for a SK and DEX for a tailor, but is worthless other than that.HOWEVER, these shoulders ROCK for an INT caster due to the nice mana, high INT, and high DEX(depending on if you believe its important, no really clear test on this have shown it for a caster), the stamina is also great for necromantic health so they can use their conversion spells (ie: lich) to convert into mana. <br>     Engraved bone pauldrons are achieved through a very easy 30 minute quest and run under 400pp generally, acrylia is harder to obtain because its new, but at 45 you could take down the mobs for the tailoring components easy and turn in the components to your local tailor and maybe suppliment them with some cash to create these nice shoulders for you.<br>     I hope this info and my terrible english have helped some, I'd recommend looking for these mantles as they are all (minus jade/absorbtion) fairly easy to obtain. <br>&nbsp;<br>"A stranger is a friend you just haven't met yet"<br>60th Virtuoso of Povar</td></tr>
